    <p><em parentName="p">{`This guide assumes you have followed the steps of both `}<a parentName="em" {...{
          "href": "/docs/installation"
        }}>{`installing`}</a>{` and `}<a parentName="em" {...{
          "href": "/docs/firststeps"
        }}>{`setting up`}</a>{` WordWeaver. You are therefore assumed to have some knowledge and understanding of `}<a parentName="em" {...{
          "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git"
        }}>{`Git`}</a>{`, `}<a parentName="em" {...{
          "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Command-line_interface"
        }}>{`Command Line`}</a>{`, `}<a parentName="em" {...{
          "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)"
        }}>{`Python`}</a>{`, and `}<a parentName="em" {...{
          "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Docker_(software)"
        }}>{`Docker`}</a>{`. In order to deploy to a production environment, it's also recommended that you have some familiarity with `}<a parentName="em" {...{
          "href": "https://www.nginx.com/resources/wiki/"
        }}>{`nginx`}</a>{`. All of these tools are used in this guide`}</em></p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "the-basic-layout"
    }}>{`The basic layout`}</h2>
    <p>{`Before we dig in, have a look at the directory tree below. Please refer to it throughout this guide.`}</p>
    <div {...{
      "className": "admonition admonition-note alert alert--secondary"
    }}><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-heading"
      }}><h5 parentName="div"><span parentName="h5" {...{
            "className": "admonition-icon"
          }}><svg parentName="span" {...{
              "xmlns": "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg",
              "width": "14",
              "height": "16",
              "viewBox": "0 0 14 16"
            }}><path parentName="svg" {...{
                "fillRule": "evenodd",
                "d": "M6.3 5.69a.942.942 0 0 1-.28-.7c0-.28.09-.52.28-.7.19-.18.42-.28.7-.28.28 0 .52.09.7.28.18.19.28.42.28.7 0 .28-.09.52-.28.7a1 1 0 0 1-.7.3c-.28 0-.52-.11-.7-.3zM8 7.99c-.02-.25-.11-.48-.31-.69-.2-.19-.42-.3-.69-.31H6c-.27.02-.48.13-.69.31-.2.2-.3.44-.31.69h1v3c.02.27.11.5.31.69.2.2.42.31.69.31h1c.27 0 .48-.11.69-.31.2-.19.3-.42.31-.69H8V7.98v.01zM7 2.3c-3.14 0-5.7 2.54-5.7 5.68 0 3.14 2.56 5.7 5.7 5.7s5.7-2.55 5.7-5.7c0-3.15-2.56-5.69-5.7-5.69v.01zM7 .98c3.86 0 7 3.14 7 7s-3.14 7-7 7-7-3.12-7-7 3.14-7 7-7z"
              }}></path></svg></span>{`note`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`If there are files in your cloned version that are not in the tree below, you do not have to worry about them unless you are very comfortable with Python and Docker and want to customize your application beyond what is covered in this documentation.`}</p></div></div>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`.
+-- volumes
|   +-- db
+-- wordweaver
|       +-- test
|       +-- wordweaver
|           +-- data
|               +-- fr
|                   +-- __init__.py
