+-- Dockerfile
+-- env-backend.env
+-- env-couch.env
+-- init-letsencrypt.sh
+-- local.ini
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`When deploying just to a development environment (the default) there are only two services being composed by docker, the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#backend-wordweaver"
      }}>{`backend`}</a>{` and the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#db-couchdb"
      }}>{`database`}</a>{`. To deploy to production, we also need a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#certbot"
      }}>{`certbot`}</a>{` service and a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#reverse-proxy-nginx"
      }}>{`reverse proxy`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "backend-wordweaver"
    }}>{`Backend (WordWeaver)`}</h2>
    <p>{`This is the main configurable service. It is the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`wordweaver`}</inlineCode>{` Python package and API.`}</p>
    <p>{`Every WordWeaver has its data separated into 4 main sections and must be in JSON format. To add your data, create a new folder in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`wordweaver/wordweaver/data`}</inlineCode>{`. It should be named after your language's `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://iso639-3.sil.org/"
      }}>{`ISO 639-3 code`}</a>{`. You will need to add 6 files (including a blank `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`__init__.py`}</inlineCode>{` file). The following sections describe the remaining 5 files.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "verbs"
    }}>{`Verbs`}</h3>
    <p>{`You must have data related to the verb roots available in your WordWeaver in a single `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`verbs.json`}</inlineCode>{` file. Your verbs should be a JSON array of objects. Minimally, each verb in your verbs array must have unique `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`tag`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`gloss`}</inlineCode>{`, and `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`classes`}</inlineCode>{` keys. `}</p>
    <p>{`Default Definition:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-python"
      }}>{`class Verb(BaseModel):
    ''' Required '''
    gloss: str = ''
    tag: str = ''
    classes: List[str] = []
`}</code></pre>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "tag"
    }}>{`tag`}</h4>
    <p>{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`tag`}</inlineCode>{` is the unique identifier for that verb. It must also be a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19335215/what-is-a-slug"
      }}>{`slug`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "gloss"
    }}>{`gloss`}</h4>
    <p>{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`gloss`}</inlineCode>{` is the display form.`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "classes"
    }}>{`classes`}</h4>
    <p>{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`classes`}</inlineCode>{` key is an array of strings that are class names to apply to that verb.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "pronouns"
    }}>{`Pronouns`}</h3>
    <p>{`You must have data related to the pronouns available in your WordWeaver in a single `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`pronouns.json`}</inlineCode>{` file.`}</p>
    <p>{`Default Definition:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-python"
      }}>{`class Pronoun(BaseModel):
    ''' Required '''
    gloss: str = ''
    obj_gloss: str = ''
    tag: str = ''
`}</code></pre>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "tag-1"
    }}>{`tag`}</h4>
    <p>{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`tag`}</inlineCode>{` is the unique identifier for that verb. It must also be a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19335215/what-is-a-slug"
      }}>{`slug`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "gloss-1"
    }}>{`gloss`}</h4>
    <p>{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`gloss`}</inlineCode>{` is the subject display form.`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "obj_gloss"
    }}>{`obj_gloss`}</h4>
    <p>{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`gloss`}</inlineCode>{` is the object display form.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "options"
    }}>{`Options`}</h3>
    <p>{`You must have all other options related to your data available in a single `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`options.json`}</inlineCode>{` file.`}</p>
    <p>{`Default Definition:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-python"
      }}>{`class Option(BaseModel):
    ''' Required '''
    gloss: str = ''
    tag: str = ''
    type: str = ''
`}</code></pre>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "tag-2"
    }}>{`tag`}</h4>
    <p>{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`tag`}</inlineCode>{` is the unique identifier for that verb. It must also be a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19335215/what-is-a-slug"
      }}>{`slug`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "gloss-2"
    }}>{`gloss`}</h4>
    <p>{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`gloss`}</inlineCode>{` is the display form.`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "type"
    }}>{`type`}</h4>
    <p>{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`type`}</inlineCode>{` allows for categorization of options (ex. tense, aspect etc)`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "conjugations"
    }}>{`Conjugations`}</h3>
    <p>{`You must have data related to the conjugations available in your WordWeaver in a single `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`conjugations.json`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`Each conjugation consists of an `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`input`}</inlineCode>{` and an `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`output`}</inlineCode>{`:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-python"
      }}>{`class ResponseObject(BaseModel):
    input: ConjugationInput
    output: Conjugation
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`input`}</inlineCode>{` is an object that includes the tag values for each related `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`verb`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`pronoun`}</inlineCode>{`, and `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`option`}</inlineCode>{`:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-python"
      }}>{`class ConjugationInput(BaseModel):
    root: str
    option: str
    agent: str
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`output`}</inlineCode>{` is a list of objects containing response morphemes:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-python"
      }}>{`Conjugation = List[ResponseMorpheme]
`}</code></pre>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-python"
      }}>{`class ResponseMorpheme(BaseModel):
    position: Optional[int]
    value: Optional[str]
    gloss: Optional[str]
    english: Optional[str]
    type: Optional[List[str]]
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Response morphemes are units that can be concatenated into `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Tiers`}</inlineCode>{`. Tiers are defined in the WordWeaver UI and concatenate response morphemes based on a provided key. They also join them with a provided `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`separator`}</inlineCode>{` value. `}</p>
    <p>{`For example, a possible conjugation:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-json"
      }}>{`{
    "input": {
        "root": "courir",
        "option": "indicatif-present",
        "agent": "2-pl"
    },
    "output": [
        {
            "position": 0,
            "value": "cour",
            "type": [
                "root"
            ]
        },
        {
            "position": 1,
            "value": "ez",
            "type": [
                "ending"
            ]
        }
    ]
}
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Here, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`courir`}</inlineCode>{` must be a tag of a verb defined in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`verbs.json`}</inlineCode>{`. `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`indicatif-present`}</inlineCode>{` must be a tag of an option defined in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`options.json`}</inlineCode>{` and `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`2-pl`}</inlineCode>{` must be a tag of a pronoun defined in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`pronouns.json`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`Here is an example of two possible tiers that could be defined from this type of data in a WordWeaver UI:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-typescript"
      }}>{`export const TIERS: Tier[] = [
  {
    name: "display",
    key: "value",
    position: 0,
    separator: ""
  },
  {
    name: "breakdown",
    key: "value",
    position: 1,
    separator: "-"
  }
];
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Here, the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`display`}</inlineCode>{` tier value would be `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`courez`}</inlineCode>{` while the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`breakdown`}</inlineCode>{` tier would be `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`cour-ez`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "edit-cors-rules"
    }}>{`Edit CORS rules`}</h3>
    <p>{`Your CORS rules are defined in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`wordweaver/wordweaver/main.py`}</inlineCode>{`. You can edit allowable origins, methods and headers here.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "update-type-definitions"
    }}>{`Update Type Definitions`}</h3>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "edit-routes"
    }}>{`Edit routes`}</h3>
    <p>{`Your routes are defined in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`wordweaver/wordweaver/main.py`}</inlineCode>{`. By default, there are routes to the auto-built API documentation at `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`/docs`}</inlineCode>{`, as well as your `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`options`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`pronouns`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`verbs`}</inlineCode>{`, and `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`conjugations`}</inlineCode>{` resources, prefixed by `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`/api/v1`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "db-couchdb"
    }}>{`DB (CouchDB)`}</h2>
    <p>{`Most setups will not need to edit any configuration of your database. Some default settings are declared in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`local.ini`}</inlineCode>{` which is copied to the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`db`}</inlineCode>{` service container and saved as a volume in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`volumes/db/local.ini`}</inlineCode>{` after running `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`docker-compose build`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
    <div {...{
      "className": "admonition admonition-important alert alert--info"
    }}><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-heading"
      }}><h5 parentName="div"><span parentName="h5" {...{
            "className": "admonition-icon"
          }}><svg parentName="span" {...{
              "xmlns": "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg",
              "width": "14",
              "height": "16",
              "viewBox": "0 0 14 16"
            }}><path parentName="svg" {...{
                "fillRule": "evenodd",
                "d": "M7 2.3c3.14 0 5.7 2.56 5.7 5.7s-2.56 5.7-5.7 5.7A5.71 5.71 0 0 1 1.3 8c0-3.14 2.56-5.7 5.7-5.7zM7 1C3.14 1 0 4.14 0 8s3.14 7 7 7 7-3.14 7-7-3.14-7-7-7zm1 3H6v5h2V4zm0 6H6v2h2v-2z"
              }}></path></svg></span>{`important`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`It is recommended that you edit the username and password in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`env-couch.env`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p></div></div>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "reverse-proxy-nginx"
    }}>{`Reverse Proxy (nginx)`}</h2>
    <p><em parentName="p">{`This is only required for deploying to production environments`}</em></p>
    <p>{`The default nginx configuration is very basic. It is configured to work with your Let's Encrypt SSL certification, and it is also configured to force redirects to https.`}</p>
    <p>{`The configuration is defined as a template `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`volumes/reverse/nginx/conf/wordweaver.template`}</inlineCode>{` that is formatted with your domain name as defined in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`.env`}</inlineCode></p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "certbot"
    }}>{`Certbot`}</h2>
    <p><em parentName="p">{`This is only required for deploying to production environments`}</em></p>
    <p>{`Certbot manages your SSL cert. We recommend using `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://letsencrypt.org/"
      }}>{`Let's Encrypt`}</a>{`. After securing your VPS, ensuring Docker is available, and cloning your repo onto your VPS, do the following steps to set up automated renewals of your SSL cert.`}</p>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Change the email and domain in `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`.env`}</inlineCode></li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`On your VPS, run `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`init-letsencrypt.sh`}</inlineCode>{` to get an SSL cert for your site`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Spin up your WordWeaver by running `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up`}</inlineCode></li>
    </ol>
    <div {...{
      "className": "admonition admonition-important alert alert--info"
    }}><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-heading"
      }}><h5 parentName="div"><span parentName="h5" {...{
            "className": "admonition-icon"
          }}><svg parentName="span" {...{
              "xmlns": "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg",
              "width": "14",
              "height": "16",
              "viewBox": "0 0 14 16"
            }}><path parentName="svg" {...{
                "fillRule": "evenodd",
                "d": "M7 2.3c3.14 0 5.7 2.56 5.7 5.7s-2.56 5.7-5.7 5.7A5.71 5.71 0 0 1 1.3 8c0-3.14 2.56-5.7 5.7-5.7zM7 1C3.14 1 0 4.14 0 8s3.14 7 7 7 7-3.14 7-7-3.14-7-7-7zm1 3H6v5h2V4zm0 6H6v2h2v-2z"
              }}></path></svg></span>{`important`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`Your DNS records will have to be set up to point to your VPS`}</p></div></div>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

;
MDXContent.isMDXComponent = true;
